{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"avid-tile-beard","description":"## Why\n\nThe T2 semantic-resolution tier (epic `850f`) was deferred out of the v1 code-grounding floor as a\nplaceholder with three candidate backends and unresolved security/determinism tradeoffs. Before any\ncode lands, the selection and the confirm-only policy must be recorded as a durable decision, and the\nIaC grounding lane (a different domain) must be split out so it is not silently folded into this epic.\nThis story produces that record; S2/S3 implement against it.\n\n## What\n\n- Add an ADR at `docs/adr/00NN-code-grounding-t2-semantic-resolution.md` (next free ADR number) that\n  records:\n  - **Decision:** v1 T2 backend = one-shot compiler/checker-CLI diagnostics, first language Python via\n    `pyright --outputjson`. LSP-client-library and containerized/hermetic tiers are **deferred** (with\n    their cost/security/determinism tradeoffs stated: LSP multiplies per-language server/runtime/config\n    surface; containerized needs an egress-locked single-tenant microVM sandbox because building\n    untrusted client repos is arbitrary code execution).\n  - **Confirm-only mapping:** a T2 `refuted` is emitted only when the checker ran cleanly (file has no\n    import-resolution diagnostics = environment built) and there is no diagnostic at the reference;\n    every other case (tool-absent / unsupported-lang / no-file / parse-error / timeout / crash /\n    env-not-built / diagnostic-present) is `abstain` with a closed structured reason. T2 never asserts\n    an absence and never sits on a deterministic blocking path.\n  - **Minimal-seam decision (Rule-of-Three):** with one concrete backend, no `T2Backend` Protocol +\n    plugin registry — S2 ships a single `refute_semantic()` dispatch function selected by config. A\n    future backend adds a name + a branch.\n  - **Consumers unchanged:** T2 records reuse the existing three-valued contract and closed\n    vocabularies (`TIER_T2` already exists), so `5fd2`/`9da1` consumers need no edit.\n- Reference the ADR from `docs/grounding.md` (a one-line pointer under the tiers section) so the design\n  is discoverable from the grounding doc.\n- Create a **sibling epic** for the IaC grounding lane (`terraform validate` = IaC T1, Registry\n  provider/module existence = IaC T0, `terraform plan` = IaC T2) and `link <iac-epic> 850f relates_to`\n  so the split is recorded in the graph.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope: the ADR document, the `docs/grounding.md` pointer, and the sibling IaC epic + link. Out of\nscope: any `src/` change (that is S2/S3) — this is a design/doc-only story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/adr/00NN-code-grounding-t2-semantic-resolution.md` exists, follows the repo's ADR format\n      (matches a sibling ADR's structure), and records the decision, the confirm-only mapping, the\n      minimal-seam (no-registry) rationale, and the LSP/containerized deferral with tradeoffs.\n- [ ] `docs/grounding.md` links to the new ADR from its tiers/T2 section.\n- [ ] A sibling epic for the IaC grounding lane exists and is linked `relates_to` epic `850f`, with a\n      description scoping the IaC T0/T1/T2 tiers.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes; the change touches only `docs/` (no `src/` edits).","id":"2ee4-27a3-2cfa-4910","parent_id":"850f-bf87-8600-4af6","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"T2 grounding S1: ADR — select pyright compiler-CLI diagnostics backend + split IaC lane to sibling epic"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783125393535099001,"uuid":"60cd0e92-bfaa-4570-8bc0-5f50f9686a43"}